
 Personal Finance & Digital Wallet Mobile App



 1. Project Overview

Project Name: Personal Finance & Digital Wallet App
Client Type: FinTech / Digital Payments Platform
Designer Role: UI/UX Designer (UX Research, Interaction Design, Visual Design)
Platform: Mobile App (Android & iOS)

 Objective

To design a secure, intuitive, and engaging personal finance application that allows users to manage balances, perform transactions, track spending, and earn rewards—while maintaining trust, simplicity, and speed.



 2. Problem Statement

Users often face challenges with finance apps such as:

. Complex dashboards that overwhelm users
. Poor visibility of balances and transactions
. Low engagement after basic usage
. Confusing settings and security controls

Design Goal: Create a clean, user-friendly finance app that enables quick financial actions, clear spending insights, and long-term user engagement through rewards and gamification.



 3. Target Users & Personas

 Primary Users

1. Young Professionals – Daily payments & budgeting
2. Students – Expense tracking & rewards
3. Frequent Digital Payment Users – Transfers & bill payments
4. Casual Finance Users – Simple money management

 User Needs

. Quick access to balance & actions
. Clear transaction history
. Spending insights
. Strong security & privacy
. Reward-driven engagement



 4. User Journey

1. Login / Biometric Authentication
   ↓
2. View Dashboard (Balance & Actions)
   ↓
3. Perform Transactions (Send, Receive, Pay Bills)
   ↓
4. Review Transactions & Insights
   ↓
5. Explore Rewards & Referrals
   ↓
6. Manage Settings & Security



 5. Information Architecture

 Bottom Navigation

. Home
. Cards / Transactions
. Rewards
. Account

 Settings Structure

. Account Info
. Payment Methods
. Notifications
. Security
. Language & Theme
. Help & Support



 6. Design System

 Color Palette

. Primary: Blue / Indigo (Trust & Finance)
. Accent: Green (Positive transactions), Red (Expenses)
. Neutral: White & Light Grey

 Typography

. Headings: Bold, clean sans-serif
. Body Text: Regular, readable
. Amounts: High-contrast, semi-bold

 UI Principles

. Speed-focused interactions
. Clear visual hierarchy
. Minimal distractions
. Trust & security first



 7. Screen-wise UX & UI Breakdown

 7.1 Home Dashboard

Purpose: Quick financial overview

Key Elements:

. Greeting & personalization
. Total and available balance
. Primary actions (Send, Receive, Add Money, Pay Bills)
. Recent transactions

UX Decisions:

. Important actions placed above the fold
. Transaction categories for quick recognition
. Clean layout to reduce cognitive load



 7.2 Transactions & Insights

Content:

. Recent transaction list
. Monthly spending insights
. Categorized expenses

UX Strategy:

. Simple transaction cards
. Visual spending summaries
. Easy-to-understand insights text



 7.3 Rewards Section

Features:

. Scratch & Win cards
. Cashback coins
. Vouchers
. Referral rewards

UX Rationale:

. Gamification to increase engagement
. Clear reward values
. Progress indicators for motivation



 7.4 Referral Program

Purpose: Organic user growth

UX Decisions:

. Simple explanation of rewards
. Clear CTA to share app
. Bonus progress tracking



 7.5 Account & Settings

Sections:

. Profile & account info
. Payment methods
. Notifications
. Security settings

Security Features:

. Biometric login
. Password change
. Linked devices management

UX Approach:

. Grouped settings categories
. Clear labels & icons
. Safety-first microcopy



 8. Accessibility & Usability Considerations

. Large tappable buttons
. Clear color contrast for amounts
. Icon + text labels
. Simple language
. Error prevention for financial actions



 9. Engagement & Gamification Strategy

. Scratch cards for instant rewards
. Cashback coins for repeat usage
. Referral bonuses
. Progress tracking to encourage task completion



 10. Tools Used

. Design: Figma
. Prototyping: Interactive mobile prototypes
. UX Research: FinTech app benchmarking



 11. Future Enhancements

. Budget planning tools
. AI-powered spending insights
. Investment & savings goals
. Dark mode
. Voice-assisted payments



 12. Conclusion

This UI/UX design delivers a balance between functionality, security, and engagement. The clean interface ensures fast financial actions, while rewards and insights encourage long-term user retention and trust.



Designed by: Sanskrati Agrawal
Role: UI/UX Designer
